The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, February 24, 2003  Calcutta Column
				 																																									The toll collection centre on Vidyasagar Setu definitely requires a whitewash. The walls are stained with betel juice. Moreover, the road on the bridge, too, requires urgent repairs. Frequent mishaps, involving heavy vehicles, have damaged the stretch. Constables posted on the bridge are always welcome, but not without the basic amenities, like a shade or a toilet. 				 																																									Sumant Poddar,				 																																									Kyd Street.				 																																									Dirty waterbodies and muddy canals in the Salt Lake, Lake Town and Dum Dum areas are breeding grounds of mosquitoes. Insecticides need to be sprayed without further delay.				 																																									Bhupen Bose,				 																																									Dum Dum.
